# TruthLens - Fake News Detector

A machine learning based fake news detection web application built using Python, Streamlit, NLP, and Scikit-learn.

## Features
- Detects fake and real news articles
- Modern futuristic UI using Streamlit
- TF-IDF vectorization
- Logistic Regression model
- Confidence score visualization

## Tech Stack
- Python
- Streamlit
- Scikit-learn
- NLTK
- TF-IDF

## Machine Learning Pipeline
1. Text preprocessing
2. Stopword removal
3. Lemmatization
4. TF-IDF vectorization
5. Logistic Regression classification

## Accuracy
~98.8% Accuracy on test dataset

## Files
- `app.py` → Streamlit frontend
- `train_model.py` → Model training script
- `model.pkl` → Trained ML model
- `vectorizer.pkl` → TF-IDF vectorizer

## Run Locally

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
python train_model.py
python -m streamlit run app.py
